summary:
The Security Council, recalling its relevant resolutions, stresses that Gaza is an integral part of the territory occupied in 1967 and will be part of the Palestinian state. The Council expresses grave concern at the escalation of violence, heavy civilian casualties, and the deepening humanitarian crisis in Gaza.

The Council calls for:

1. An immediate, durable, and fully respected ceasefire, leading to the full withdrawal of Israeli forces from Gaza;
2. Unimpeded provision and distribution of humanitarian assistance throughout Gaza;
3. Initiatives to create and open humanitarian corridors for sustained delivery of humanitarian aid;

The Council also:

* Calls on Member States to support international efforts to alleviate the humanitarian and economic situation in Gaza;
* Condemns all violence and hostilities directed against civilians and acts of terrorism;
* Calls upon Member States to intensify efforts to provide arrangements and guarantees in Gaza to sustain a durable ceasefire and calm;
* Encourages tangible steps towards intra-Palestinian reconciliation;
* Calls for renewed and urgent efforts to achieve a comprehensive peace based on the vision of two democratic States, Israel and Palestine, living side by side in peace with secure and recognized borders;

